According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Artificial Intelligence-based Beauty Products market was valued at USD 4.80 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 5.90 billion in 2026 to USD 20.15 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 16.6% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing robust growth as consumers increasingly embrace AI-powered skincare, makeup, haircare, and smart beauty devices that deliver highly personalized experiences. Continuous advancements in machine learning, computer vision, augmented reality (AR), and predictive analytics are transforming the beauty industry by enabling customized product recommendations, virtual try-on experiences, intelligent skin diagnostics, and AI-assisted product formulation.
